content:
(Update: it's due to the file being imported by another file on master.)

After deleting the file Mathlib.Algebra.Squarefree.UniqueFactorizationDomain.lean and removing it from Mathlib.lean, CI fails at the "build mathlib" step with the message:

Run liskin/gh-problem-matcher-wrap@v2
/usr/bin/bash -o pipefail -c env LEAN_ABORT_ON_PANIC=1 lake build -KCI | tee stdout.log
error: 'Mathlib.Algebra.Squarefree.UniqueFactorizationDomain': no such file or directory (error code: 2)
file: ./././Mathlib/Algebra/Squarefree/UniqueFactorizationDomain.lean
Error: The process '/usr/bin/bash' failed with exit code 1

In the "get cache" step, there is a warning (repeated twice):

Run lake exe cache clean
Warning: ./Mathlib/Algebra/Squarefree/UniqueFactorizationDomain.lean not found. Skipping all files that depend on it
Warning: ./Mathlib/Algebra/Squarefree/UniqueFactorizationDomain.lean not found. Skipping all files that depend on it
Attempting to download 4226 file(s)

Is this related to recent changes in cache handling?
Are you sure you deleted all imports of it?
Oh indeed it has been imported by another file in the meantime. Thanks!
Junyan Xu has marked this topic as resolved.
